==English==
===Etymology===
Of uncertain origin; theories include:
* an [[initialism]] from "we own the other team";
* an [[onomatopoeia]] representing the sound of capture sirens from online [[capture the flag game]]s;
* a [[blend]] of '''[[wow]]''' and '''[[loot]]''';
* a [[leetspeak]] mutation of '''[[whoo]]''', '''[[what]]''' or '''[[root]]''';
* a [[corruption]] of '''[[root]]''', shouted by [[hacker]]s when they obtain [[root]]-level access in a targeted system.
The [[w:w00t|Wikipedia article]] has further suggestions.

===Pronunciation===
*{{AHD|wo͞ot}}, {{IPA|/wuːt/}}, {{SAMPA|/wu:t/}}

===Interjection===
{{wikipedia}}
'''w00t'''!
#{{slang}} Used to express [[joy]], particularly that felt during [[success]] or [[victory]].
#{{slang}} (''followed by a question mark'') What?

====Usage notes====
'''w00t''' is used in [[leet]] as part of Internet slang.

